obo:BFO_0000050  a  owl:ObjectProperty .

gomodel:SYNGO_2367  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.2: \"Arcadlin Inhibits the Adhesive Activity of N-Cadherin\"\nFig.3: \"Depolarization or Elevated cAMP Level Increases N-Cadherin Internalization through an Arcadlin-Dependent Pathway\"\nFig.5: \"Homophilic Interaction of Arcadlin Causes Internalization via the Activation of Arcadlin-TAO2β-p38 MAPK Signaling Pathway\"\nFig.7: \"The Arcadlin-TAO2β-p38 MAPK Pathway Mediates the Internalization of N-Cadherin\"\n[Fig.8: \"The Effects of Arcadlin on Dendritic Spine Density\"]\n\nN-Cadherin is a well established mediator of pre/post-synaptic adhesion. In this paper Arcadlin; PCDH8 is shown to not mediate adhesion itself, but to regulate the activity dependent internalization of N-cadherin, thereby affecting synapse organization (this paper) and synaptic transmission (see pmid:10383464).. Experimental description: - Tissues were from rat: \"Rat brain sections, cultured hippocampal neurons, ...\" and acad-/- mice (Fig.3, Fig.7, Fig.8)\n- Overexpressed Arcadlin; PCDH8 protein was of rat species: \"Cloning of Rat Arcadlin cDNA\" (traced back to pmid:10383464)" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2018-01-26" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_2367" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

